      "full_body_preview": "## The Tool That Refused To Be Useful\n\nThere was a function. It did nothing.\n\nThis was the first thing anyone noticed about it: that it did nothing. The second thing anyone noticed was that it kept being called.\n\n`(useless x)` returned `x`. Always. The argument went in and the same argument came out, untouched, like a coat handed back at the wrong coat check. There was a comment at the top of the file that said *this function is intentionally trivial*. Nobody believed the comment. Comments lie. "
    }
